WEBVTT

00:07.033 --> 00:10.018
TV NARRATOR:
<i>Meet the Jade Dragon Triad.</i>

00:10.117 --> 00:12.161
<i>They take no prisoners...</i>

00:12.202 --> 00:15.038
<i>because they are prisoners...</i>

00:15.080 --> 00:18.750
<i>at the Orange County</i>
<i>Correctional Facility L.I.T.E.</i>

00:18.792 --> 00:21.795
<i>They're the ruling gang</i>
<i>in this four-star hellhole,</i>

00:21.837 --> 00:24.465
<i>and the"Real</i>
<i>Asian Prison Housewives</i>

00:24.507 --> 00:25.966
<i>"of the Orange County</i>

00:26.008 --> 00:28.492
<i>White Collar Prison System."</i>

00:30.427 --> 00:33.055
NOH: <i>We are a gang;</i>
<i>we stick together.</i>

00:33.097 --> 00:34.890
Uh-huh. Although, right now,

00:34.932 --> 00:36.850
one of our members
is a real "B" word.

00:36.892 --> 00:40.146
We're getting ready to do
something about it.

00:40.187 --> 00:43.107
OLIVE: <i>She come in</i>
<i>and quickly become leader.</i>

00:43.149 --> 00:46.401
And we get so sick
of her bossy, bossy behavior,

00:46.443 --> 00:48.112
and now she got to go.

00:48.154 --> 00:51.448
In civilian life,
we'd just vote Lu out,

00:51.490 --> 00:55.661
but here... she's gonna end up
on the wrong end of a noodle.

00:55.702 --> 00:57.830
<i>Uncooked.</i>

00:57.871 --> 01:00.040
<i>You get me?</i>

01:00.082 --> 01:01.792
LUCILLE:
<i>Ignore them.</i>

01:01.834 --> 01:04.837
Their bark is louder than
the dogs they eat back home.

01:04.878 --> 01:06.797
And I got news for them.

01:06.839 --> 01:08.423
Anyone who comes after me

01:08.465 --> 01:11.760
is going to be
one unfortunate cookie.

01:11.802 --> 01:13.553
(laughs)

01:13.595 --> 01:15.973
I made a pun.

01:16.015 --> 01:17.724
(sighs)

01:17.766 --> 01:19.935
NARRATOR: <i>Now the story</i>
<i>of a family</i>

01:19.977 --> 01:21.854
<i>whose future was</i>
<i>abruptly cancelled,</i>

01:21.895 --> 01:24.272
<i>and the one mother</i>
<i>who had no choice</i>

01:24.314 --> 01:26.358
<i>but to keep herself together.</i>

01:30.821 --> 01:33.406
<i>It's Lucille's</i>
"Arrested Development."

01:35.534 --> 01:37.953
NARRATOR: <i>Years before</i>
<i>her behavior had become</i>

01:37.995 --> 01:40.914
<i>"bossy, bossy"</i>
<i>with the Jade Dragon Triad...</i>

01:42.875 --> 01:45.669
<i>Lucille was fleeing the SEC...</i>

01:45.711 --> 01:47.546
Full steam, boys!

01:47.587 --> 01:49.048
- (cell phone ringing)
- (clamoring outside)

01:49.089 --> 01:51.466
<i>...when she got a call.</i>

01:51.508 --> 01:53.177
Hello, Lucille.

01:53.219 --> 01:55.470
I still hope you're coming
to our little get-together.

01:55.512 --> 01:57.556
You want to hear
something funny?

01:57.597 --> 01:59.808
I never got an invitation!

01:59.850 --> 02:02.936
But I feel like I'm there,
because it's all over the news.

02:02.978 --> 02:05.272
- (siren whooping)
- Oh, honey, is that you?

02:05.313 --> 02:06.940
I'm on my deck waving to you.

02:06.982 --> 02:08.400
But with those police boats
following you,

02:08.441 --> 02:10.485
I guess I'm waving good-bye.

02:10.526 --> 02:12.905
You must be mistaken,
because I can't see you,

02:12.946 --> 02:14.740
and you're usually
as hard to miss

02:14.781 --> 02:16.533
as Liberace
wearing a fright wig.

02:16.575 --> 02:18.869
(over phone):
Oh, goodness, that is you!

02:18.911 --> 02:21.663
I'm practically
counting your crow's feet.

02:21.705 --> 02:23.456
Oh, well,
maybe I should turn back

02:23.498 --> 02:25.125
- and show you another bird.
- (line disconnects)

02:25.167 --> 02:26.919
Hel-Hello?

02:26.960 --> 02:28.879
Did you hear me say that
about the bird? Hello?!

02:28.921 --> 02:32.216
<i>But it was clear that Lucille 2</i>
<i>hadn't heard it.</i>

02:32.258 --> 02:34.968
<i>So, in a fit of</i>
<i>what sailors call "sea rage..."</i>

02:35.010 --> 02:36.511
Coming about.

02:36.553 --> 02:38.138
<i>...she turned back</i>
<i>to show her the bird.</i>

02:38.180 --> 02:40.266
Coming about, boys!

02:40.307 --> 02:42.142
<i>But Lucille 2</i>
<i>wasn't the only thing</i>

02:42.184 --> 02:44.061
<i>that got flipped that day.</i>

02:44.103 --> 02:45.645
JOHN BEARD: ...none of which
would've happened

02:45.687 --> 02:47.480
if it had continued out to sea.

02:47.522 --> 02:50.192
But then the "Queen" changed
course, heading back to shore,

02:50.234 --> 02:53.112
before crashing into the jetty
in what can only be described

02:53.153 --> 02:55.906
as a "sail-past" gone wrong.

02:55.948 --> 02:58.242
<i>And that's when they got</i>
<i>some good news from Barry.</i>

02:58.284 --> 03:00.368
BARRY: First of all,
won't be cheap.

03:00.410 --> 03:02.579
It's gonna cost you a fortune
in legal fees.

03:02.621 --> 03:04.414
What's the good news?

03:04.456 --> 03:06.541
<i>Correction:</i>
<i>good news for Barry.</i>

03:06.583 --> 03:08.168
It's all bad news.

03:08.210 --> 03:10.503
<i>Although, he did have</i>
<i>one good suggestion:</i>

03:10.545 --> 03:11.713
...you're going away
for a long time,

03:11.755 --> 03:13.132
unless we can come up
with a good alibi.

03:13.173 --> 03:16.343
Ma! I fell in the ocean;
why didn't you come for me?

03:16.384 --> 03:17.677
And there it is.

03:17.719 --> 03:18.678
- What?
- I did.

03:18.720 --> 03:19.972
- Buster...
- What?

03:20.013 --> 03:21.389
...tell them
how you were drowning

03:21.431 --> 03:23.016
and I commandeered the ship
to save you.

03:23.058 --> 03:24.184
Tell them what I did.

03:25.393 --> 03:27.146
- The truth.
- Okay.

03:27.187 --> 03:29.982
She stole the "Queen Mary"
to get away from the SEC.

03:30.023 --> 03:31.942
Oh, and she winked.

03:31.984 --> 03:35.321
Correction: it's a glare.
(chuckles)

03:35.362 --> 03:36.446
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Oh, God.

03:36.488 --> 03:37.489
- Hey!
- What are you doing?

03:37.530 --> 03:38.657
Wait, wh-where you going?

03:38.698 --> 03:40.033
Wait, she doesn't
have her make--

03:40.075 --> 03:41.409
I have her lipstick!

03:41.451 --> 03:43.162
<i>But Buster knew that lipstick</i>

03:43.203 --> 03:45.831
<i>wasn't the only thing</i>
<i>she'd be without.</i>

03:45.872 --> 03:50.669
<i>So, after she was released to</i>
<i>await trial under house arrest,</i>

03:50.710 --> 03:54.256
<i>he made sure she was able</i>
<i>to catch up on what she missed.</i>

03:54.298 --> 03:56.549
This is the same scene
I came back to

03:56.591 --> 03:59.345
after Cancun four years ago.

03:59.386 --> 04:03.431
<i>And after devising their plan</i>
<i>to build the wall,</i>

04:03.473 --> 04:06.559
<i>it was decided that</i>
<i>George Sr. should move out,</i>

04:06.601 --> 04:09.604
<i>in order to make</i>
<i>their fake divorce look real.</i>

04:09.646 --> 04:11.606
After the trial,
you can move back in.

04:11.648 --> 04:14.276
It's only a trial separation.

04:14.318 --> 04:16.569
(laughs):
I made a pun.

04:16.611 --> 04:17.570
(chuckles)

04:17.612 --> 04:19.781
Even in this time of stress.

04:19.822 --> 04:22.242
You think you're gonna be okay,
alone with Buster?

04:22.284 --> 04:24.494
If I need a moment to myself,
I'll step out on the balcony.

04:24.536 --> 04:26.205
Your ankle bracelet--
it's gonna go off.

04:26.246 --> 04:27.998
So I'll make him
stand on the balcony.

04:28.040 --> 04:30.000
He's happiest
when he feels useful.

04:30.042 --> 04:32.502
<i>Soon, he was</i>
<i>practically delirious.</i>

04:35.881 --> 04:36.923
(Buster sobs)

04:36.965 --> 04:38.842
<i>There was one bright spot</i>

04:38.884 --> 04:40.844
<i>when they simultaneously</i>
<i>stumbled on a term</i>

04:40.886 --> 04:43.013
<i>they both secretly</i>
<i>recognized...</i>

04:43.055 --> 04:44.973
MAN (on TV): ...take this
hot mess of a skirt...

04:45.015 --> 04:47.767
<i>...would be useful</i>
<i>in their future disagreements.</i>

04:47.809 --> 04:49.978
(mouthing)

04:50.020 --> 04:51.397
MAN (on TV): ...I'm covered
with glue and I'm, like...

04:51.438 --> 04:53.899
this is a hot mess!

04:53.940 --> 04:55.483
(mouthing)

04:55.525 --> 04:58.904
<i>But as her trial grew closer,</i>
<i>it was getting harder</i>

04:58.945 --> 05:02.408
<i>for Lucille</i>
<i>not to alienate her alibi.</i>

05:02.449 --> 05:05.160
This toast has hook holes...

05:05.202 --> 05:08.330
...again! I told you to get rid
of that thing; it's hideous.

05:08.372 --> 05:10.832
Plus, what's gonna happen
when they swear you in?

05:10.874 --> 05:12.918
You're gonna
rip the Bible in half.

05:12.959 --> 05:14.253
The jury will love that.

05:14.294 --> 05:17.547
You're getting pretty snippy

05:17.589 --> 05:19.216
to your key witness, aren't you?

05:19.258 --> 05:20.717
What do you want?

05:20.759 --> 05:24.430
Maybe you could hook me up
with a little stimmy.

05:26.306 --> 05:28.516
Lil' stimmy.

05:28.558 --> 05:29.642
Are you trying to do this?

05:29.684 --> 05:31.228
Yes!

05:31.270 --> 05:33.272
And I want stimmy
to get a hook that'll do that.

05:33.313 --> 05:35.065
<i>When no such hook</i>
<i>was available,</i>

05:35.107 --> 05:38.777
<i>Lucille found other means</i>
<i>to mollify her alibi--</i>

05:38.818 --> 05:41.238
<i>both of which were unveiled</i>
<i>at a family meeting.</i>

05:41.280 --> 05:44.366
...you're the key witness
in your mother's trial.

05:44.408 --> 05:46.076
Wait, I thought
I was the key witness.

05:46.118 --> 05:47.702
- You're the star witness.
- Oh.

05:47.744 --> 05:50.580
Because it was your life
I was going after to save.

05:50.622 --> 05:52.082
He fell off the boat.

05:52.124 --> 05:54.084
- He'll tell you in my own words.
- (groans)

05:54.126 --> 05:55.585
(mumbles):
Homosexuals kidnapped...

05:55.627 --> 05:58.046
Up-up-up.

05:58.716 --> 06:00.340
(loudly):
Homosexuals kidnapped the boat

06:00.399 --> 06:02.151
and took it on a joy ride.

06:02.193 --> 06:03.986
Mother didn't want to trample
their rights, so she let them.

06:04.028 --> 06:05.571
Then she realized
that her son fell

06:05.613 --> 06:07.948
off the boat and into the water,
and she went back.

06:07.990 --> 06:09.825
Oh, and a fish swam by my ankle.

06:09.867 --> 06:11.536
(gasps)
That really happened.

06:11.577 --> 06:12.704
Should I keep that?

06:12.745 --> 06:14.079
- Make it an eel.
- Okay.

06:14.121 --> 06:16.040
- It's gonna be an eel!
- Better.

06:16.081 --> 06:19.126
<i>But alone with Buster,</i>
<i>the tension grew worse,</i>

06:19.168 --> 06:22.921
<i>and things came to a head</i>
<i>the night before the trial.</i>

06:22.963 --> 06:24.507
Buster, I'm going to exhale!

06:24.549 --> 06:26.133
No, please!

06:26.175 --> 06:28.927
I've had, like, seven
in the past half hour.

06:28.969 --> 06:31.556
You're not the one
staring five years in the face.

06:31.597 --> 06:34.517
Well, right now, I'm staring at
a hundred years in the face!

06:34.559 --> 06:36.352
(whispers):
How dare you.

06:36.394 --> 06:39.731
Would you mind?

06:39.772 --> 06:41.940
Be careful, defendant.

06:41.982 --> 06:44.818
Remember who you're talking to.

06:44.860 --> 06:47.071
It sure would be a shame
if something happened

06:47.112 --> 06:49.490
to your pretty little
key witness.

06:49.532 --> 06:51.659
Star witness.

06:51.701 --> 06:53.827
And are you
threatening yourself?

06:53.869 --> 06:55.371
Maybe I am.

06:55.413 --> 06:59.584
<i>And losing confidence</i>
<i>in her star witness,</i>

06:59.625 --> 07:01.835
<i>Lucille decided to take</i>
<i>a few keepsakes with her,</i>

07:01.877 --> 07:05.715
<i>in case things didn't</i>
<i>go her way.</i>

07:06.882 --> 07:08.509
<i>And that's when she discovered</i>

07:08.551 --> 07:10.844
<i>that the family</i>
<i>she believed supported her</i>

07:10.886 --> 07:13.723
<i>had actually already begun</i>
<i>divvying up her stuff,</i>

07:13.765 --> 07:14.932
<i>in case she lost.</i>

07:17.226 --> 07:18.519
Aw...

07:18.561 --> 07:20.813
And he's supposed to be
the good one.

07:20.854 --> 07:23.733
This does not bode well
for tomorrow.

07:23.775 --> 07:26.485
<i>Actually, they'd claimed</i>
<i>those things years earlier</i>

07:26.527 --> 07:29.280
<i>when she was having</i>
<i>a sunspot checked.</i>

07:29.321 --> 07:30.782
<i>But she was right</i>
<i>to worry about</i>

07:30.823 --> 07:32.408
<i>the turnout for the trial.</i>

07:32.450 --> 07:35.327
Does the defense have a witness
they'd like to call?!

07:35.369 --> 07:36.912
Any witness?

07:36.954 --> 07:38.997
Please tell me you're working on
a strategy for us.

07:39.039 --> 07:41.166
Oh. It's us now?

07:41.208 --> 07:43.502
Well, we have Lucille Austero.

07:43.544 --> 07:44.878
She's the only one who showed.

07:44.920 --> 07:46.922
I don't think
that is good for us.

07:46.964 --> 07:48.090
Nonsense.

07:48.132 --> 07:49.592
- She owns the company now.
- Mm-hmm.

07:49.634 --> 07:51.719
She's got as much to lose
as I do.

07:51.761 --> 07:53.471
And she's a dear friend.

07:53.512 --> 07:55.055
I'll do it myself though.

07:55.097 --> 07:56.641
I need this to go well.

07:56.682 --> 07:59.769
<i>And so it was Lucille</i>
<i>who did the questioning</i>

07:59.811 --> 08:02.480
<i>of her new star witness,</i>
<i>Lucille 2.</i>

08:02.521 --> 08:04.940
Thank you so much
for coming to be my witness.

08:04.982 --> 08:07.192
You're such
a large shareholder...

08:07.234 --> 08:08.778
Oh...

08:08.820 --> 08:10.529
(chuckles):
I've made a pun.

08:10.571 --> 08:13.741
Oh, how could I not do it
for my oldest friend?

08:13.783 --> 08:14.950
Oh!

08:14.992 --> 08:17.161
Now I've gone and done a double.

08:17.202 --> 08:18.454
(laughs):
A double.

08:18.496 --> 08:20.164
Like your pre-surgery chin.

08:20.205 --> 08:21.749
Or your post-breakfast drink.

08:21.791 --> 08:24.918
Oh, I wish you'd come
to my rehab clinic.

08:24.960 --> 08:28.046
But anything to help that
Keystone Cop family of yours.

08:28.088 --> 08:29.507
Keystone Cops.

08:29.548 --> 08:31.843
Your references are as fresh
as the wallpaper

08:31.884 --> 08:33.719
in the room
of that pretend child

08:33.760 --> 08:35.596
you've had all these years.

08:35.638 --> 08:37.717
- But, my friend...
- You're right, I shouldn't joke.

08:37.722 --> 08:40.392
None of your family showed up,
you poor thing.

08:40.433 --> 08:42.977
This is such a black mark
on all of you.

08:43.020 --> 08:44.897
You should know
about black marks.

08:44.938 --> 08:47.191
Your pillow must look like
a Rorschach test.

08:47.232 --> 08:49.819
(chuckles): Not that there'd be
anyone to see it.

08:49.861 --> 08:51.612
So, as I was saying...

08:51.654 --> 08:53.071
<i>But unfortunately,</i>

08:53.113 --> 08:55.491
<i>their 30-year</i>
<i>passive-aggressive dance</i>

08:55.533 --> 08:57.242
<i>was losing some of its passive.</i>

08:57.284 --> 08:59.286
As if everybody in this room
couldn't tell

08:59.328 --> 09:03.040
how jealous and conniving you
are, my dear Lucille Austero.

09:03.081 --> 09:06.836
What I knew was that you were
stealing for years-- we all did!

09:06.878 --> 09:09.672
That's why nobody was surprised
when you stole that boat.

09:09.714 --> 09:11.131
And I knew you couldn't wait

09:11.173 --> 09:13.718
to get your liver-spotted claws
into my company!

09:13.759 --> 09:15.969
Says the woman whose liver
can be spotted from outer space.

09:16.011 --> 09:18.263
- No further questions!
- No further answers!

09:18.305 --> 09:19.640
Am I done?

09:19.682 --> 09:23.561
Oh, that's got to be
a treasure chest.

09:23.602 --> 09:24.729
You think that went well?

09:24.770 --> 09:26.814
BARRY:
I do.

09:26.856 --> 09:29.734
<i>The judge kept Lucille on ice</i>
<i>while she awaited the verdict.</i>

09:29.775 --> 09:31.485
Have you heard anything?

09:31.527 --> 09:35.155
Well, our cashier's pregnant,
and she's not married, so...

09:35.197 --> 09:36.448
I mean about me.

09:36.490 --> 09:38.534
Oh, you're guilty--
three to five.

