09:47.543 --> 09:49.962
<i>Lucille was</i>
<i>checking in to her new home.</i>

09:50.003 --> 09:53.090
Hello! Oh, Mrs. Bluth is here,
for stealing the "Queen Mary."

09:53.131 --> 09:56.093
- We're so glad to have you here.
<i>- It was one of the so-called</i>

09:56.134 --> 09:57.055
<i>country club prisons...</i>

09:57.094 --> 09:59.263
So... you are here.

09:59.304 --> 10:02.015
<i>...that had become popular</i>
<i>after the Enron debacle.</i>

10:02.057 --> 10:03.434
...so you're gonna take
this hallway to the elevators,

10:03.475 --> 10:04.727
and then you're gonna
want to go...

10:04.769 --> 10:06.228
Slow down.

10:06.270 --> 10:08.188
You sound like the end
of a Cymbalta commercial.

10:08.230 --> 10:10.399
Even the lifers get confused.
Don't worry...

10:10.441 --> 10:13.193
<i>Even though it was a nice</i>
<i>prison, it was still prison.</i>

10:13.235 --> 10:14.570
...your choice of
fresh scent, sport,

10:14.612 --> 10:16.196
or floral for your delousing.

10:16.238 --> 10:18.741
Also, if you're
sexually assaulted by a guard...

10:18.783 --> 10:21.410
A $20 gratuity is appreciated?

10:21.452 --> 10:22.661
(laughs)

10:22.703 --> 10:25.038
No, but press seven
on your phone.

10:25.080 --> 10:27.792
If you go through the front
desk, it'll take forever.

10:27.833 --> 10:31.003
<i>After Lucille got settled in,</i>
<i>she received a visitor.</i>

10:31.044 --> 10:32.296
LUCILLE:
You missed my trial, George.

10:32.337 --> 10:33.505
How could you?

10:33.547 --> 10:35.215
GEORGE SR:
I told you I was sorry.

10:35.257 --> 10:37.009
I was unconscious
on the sweat lodge floor.

10:37.050 --> 10:38.051
I lost two days.

10:38.093 --> 10:39.637
I'm losing three to five years.

10:39.678 --> 10:41.931
And those are the last years,
George, the best years,

10:41.973 --> 10:44.266
where you can have sex and not
worry about getting pregnant.

10:44.308 --> 10:45.601
All right, here's the good news:

10:45.643 --> 10:47.269
they only got you
on stealing the boat.

10:47.311 --> 10:49.313
They didn't even touch us
on the financial stuff.

10:49.354 --> 10:51.398
- You're gonna get out of here.
- When?

10:51.440 --> 10:53.800
Better be before the money runs
out; this place isn't cheap.

10:53.818 --> 10:56.904
I know, and you are
running up those spa bills.

10:56.946 --> 11:00.032
The same girl who hands me
towels does the cavity checks.

11:00.073 --> 11:01.492
You tip.

11:01.533 --> 11:03.828
Barry says he can get your
sentence reduced if...

11:03.869 --> 11:07.289
you agree to leave here
and go to Lucille 2's

11:07.331 --> 11:08.791
rehab clinic.

11:08.833 --> 11:11.543
That's the bitch
that put me here.

11:11.585 --> 11:14.630
And I'm not gonna fake having
some sort of...

11:14.672 --> 11:16.256
I don't know-- alcohol problem--

11:16.298 --> 11:18.843
just so that sterile cuckoo bird
can laugh at me.

11:18.884 --> 11:20.427
I figured. Okay.

11:20.469 --> 11:23.180
I have another idea--
now, you know China Garden?

11:23.221 --> 11:24.473
I know the one by the harbor.

11:24.515 --> 11:25.516
No, this one's a person.

11:25.557 --> 11:26.725
And that one closed.

11:26.767 --> 11:29.186
China Garden's Aunt Olive

11:29.227 --> 11:31.730
is very well connected
with the Jade Triad Gang.

11:31.772 --> 11:32.982
It's a prison gang here.

11:33.024 --> 11:34.900
And believe me,
they will protect you.

11:34.942 --> 11:36.986
That's a gang?

11:37.028 --> 11:40.072
I thought they were
tech support.

11:40.113 --> 11:41.824
<i>It turned out they were a gang.</i>

11:41.866 --> 11:44.035
<i>And thanks to China Garden,</i>

11:44.076 --> 11:46.286
<i>Lucille was admitted</i>
<i>as a probationary member.</i>

11:46.328 --> 11:47.913
You play mahjong before?

11:47.955 --> 11:50.123
Our beach club used
to have a Jewish Day.

11:50.165 --> 11:51.208
Your move, Olive Garden.

11:51.249 --> 11:52.835
I can't concentrate.

11:52.877 --> 11:55.212
Playing mahjong
without cigarette is like

11:55.253 --> 11:57.297
playing video poker without...

11:57.339 --> 11:58.340
cigarette.

11:58.382 --> 12:00.258
Why are we not allowed to smoke

12:00.300 --> 12:01.844
in this stupid prison?

12:01.886 --> 12:04.763
<i>And that's</i>
<i>when Lucille made her move.</i>

12:04.805 --> 12:07.683
- I know a loophole.
- Huh?

12:07.725 --> 12:08.893
"Roop hore"?

12:08.934 --> 12:10.728
- Roop hore.
- Roop hore.

12:10.769 --> 12:12.897
<i>It was a loophole</i>
<i>that would get Lucille</i>

12:12.938 --> 12:15.273
<i>accepted as</i>
<i>a full-fledged member</i>

12:15.315 --> 12:17.943
<i>member of</i>
<i>the Jade Dragon Triad.</i>

12:17.985 --> 12:19.786
You couldn't have chosen
a harder word to say.

12:22.155 --> 12:24.658
<i>And soon</i>
<i>the Dragons were taking</i>

12:24.700 --> 12:26.744
<i>"drags on"</i>
<i>their cigarettes again.</i>

12:26.785 --> 12:28.829
There's always a way
to get what you want.

12:28.871 --> 12:32.917
My husband is a very
powerful man, Lucille Bluth.

12:32.958 --> 12:36.003
Perhaps we can help each other
get what we want.

12:36.045 --> 12:39.423
<i>And that's how Lucille found</i>
<i>a deep-pocketed investor</i>

12:39.464 --> 12:41.174
<i>to help build the wall.</i>

12:41.216 --> 12:44.845
I got Olive Garden
to offer us unlimited bread.

12:44.887 --> 12:47.890
Who better than the Chinese
to help us build a wall, right?

12:47.932 --> 12:50.851
So the Chinese will own
a piece of the wall

12:50.893 --> 12:52.227
between U.S. and Mexico?

12:52.269 --> 12:53.979
They'll own all of it,
but they'll make us

12:54.021 --> 12:56.023
very rich in the process.

12:56.065 --> 12:58.650
We just need to get Michael
to sign a release.

12:58.692 --> 13:00.569
He sold his shares,
but he could still claim

13:00.611 --> 13:01.862
that he deserves a piece.

13:01.904 --> 13:04.489
Or worse, find out
and blow the whistle.

13:04.531 --> 13:06.450
Where the hell did we go wrong
with that kid?

13:06.491 --> 13:09.202
Probably where we went wrong
with the others-- I don't know.

13:09.244 --> 13:12.123
I like the plan... I just wonder

13:12.164 --> 13:14.625
if we're not in that
treason-adjacent place

13:14.666 --> 13:17.086
where the, uh,
government will retaliate

13:17.128 --> 13:19.004
and, uh... execute us.

13:19.046 --> 13:21.882
LUCILLE: Oh, they'd never
execute a woman for this.

13:21.924 --> 13:24.322
I have a good feeling
about these people.

13:24.442 --> 13:26.637
Oh, that's good enough for me.

13:26.678 --> 13:28.346
- (George crying)
<i>- But the change in the economy</i>

13:28.388 --> 13:31.809
<i>led the government to put</i>
<i>the wall project on hold.</i>

13:31.850 --> 13:33.185
<i>And as the months passed</i>

13:33.226 --> 13:35.687
<i>and the Chinese saw</i>
<i>no progress on the wall,</i>

13:35.729 --> 13:37.106
<i>tension mounted.</i>

13:37.148 --> 13:39.942
<i>And Lucille was getting</i>
<i>more controlling.</i>

13:39.984 --> 13:41.110
She said you're fat.

13:41.152 --> 13:42.861
That's what you said, right?

13:42.903 --> 13:44.155
Or does that mean something

13:44.196 --> 13:46.445
- different in Chinese?
- No, it means "fat."

13:46.565 --> 13:48.659
You keep causing trouble,
you're going to end up

13:48.700 --> 13:51.203
- with noodles in your belly.
- I like noodles.

13:51.244 --> 13:54.123
Not this way--
very hard to digest.

13:54.165 --> 13:55.791
Ancient Chinese secret, huh?

13:55.833 --> 13:57.626
It's no secret--
we'll kill you.

13:57.668 --> 13:59.711
<i>- She was even being controlling</i>
- Did you get that?

13:59.753 --> 14:01.964
<i>of the"R.A.P.H.O.C.W.C.P.S."</i>

14:02.006 --> 14:03.674
<i>reality TV crew.</i>

14:03.715 --> 14:05.425
Do you need a clean of
her making the threat?

14:05.467 --> 14:07.011
I can lean back,
but you will come around

14:07.052 --> 14:08.637
and get my reaction, yes?

14:08.679 --> 14:11.056
Oh, I'll say it again--
we'll kill you.

14:11.098 --> 14:13.391
<i>But soon</i>
<i>the threat was made real.</i>

14:13.433 --> 14:14.558
Oh!
She's got a sharpened noodle!

14:14.689 --> 14:16.483
She's trying to noodle-stab me!

14:16.524 --> 14:17.984
- Back up!
- (people screaming)

14:18.025 --> 14:19.110
(yells)

14:20.194 --> 14:22.363
- (grunts)
- (people yelling)

14:22.405 --> 14:23.615
(blows)

14:23.657 --> 14:25.492
Aah, my eye!

14:25.533 --> 14:27.952
This will be even more
exciting if you jump cut it.

14:27.994 --> 14:29.663
Quiet!

14:29.704 --> 14:34.125
You can't just come in and have
bread for nothing around here.

14:34.167 --> 14:36.753
You have to pay bill some time.

14:36.795 --> 14:39.589
<i>It wasn't a great time to find</i>
<i>out George didn't own</i>

14:39.631 --> 14:42.592
<i>the right property</i>
<i>to build the wall on.</i>

14:42.634 --> 14:45.386
<i>- And so a new plan emerged</i>
- LUCILLE: Make sure Hebert Love

14:45.428 --> 14:47.096
comes out against the wall...

14:47.138 --> 14:50.684
<i>They needed the government</i>
<i>to kill the wall completely,</i>

14:50.725 --> 14:52.477
<i>- but pay them anyway.</i>
- As much as I'd like to stay

14:52.519 --> 14:53.645
and lay some more pipe with you,

14:53.687 --> 14:55.438
I better get moving
on this thing.

14:55.480 --> 14:57.231
We've got to make
this wall work, George.

14:57.273 --> 14:58.900
We know Lucille 2
will oppose it,

14:58.941 --> 15:01.277
we just have make sure
Herbert Love does.

15:01.318 --> 15:03.111
Oh, don't worry-- that's
why I asked Michael for help.

15:03.154 --> 15:06.574
Michael? What are you bringing
Michael into this for?

15:06.616 --> 15:08.618
The only thing he should
be doing is signing over

15:08.660 --> 15:09.744
his rights to the company.

15:09.786 --> 15:11.287
I asked him to do this as well.

15:11.329 --> 15:12.497
<i>He made it a condition</i>
<i>of the now</i>

15:12.539 --> 15:14.457
<i>four favor family pact.</i>

15:14.499 --> 15:15.709
Will you please relax?

15:15.750 --> 15:16.671
...do something for me?

15:16.710 --> 15:18.545
You know,
your mother is very hurt.

15:18.586 --> 15:20.672
You haven't visited her.
It's like you have given up

15:20.714 --> 15:22.256
- on the family business.
- I have.

15:22.298 --> 15:24.050
Yes, but not in writing.

15:24.091 --> 15:25.844
To protect all of us, visit her,

15:25.886 --> 15:28.137
sign a little something
saying it's all hers.

15:28.179 --> 15:29.472
- Will you do this, Michael?
- Yeah.

15:29.514 --> 15:30.557
But I get to make you look bad

15:30.598 --> 15:31.850
- in the movie, okay?
- Okay.

15:31.892 --> 15:32.934
- Should we settle up?
- All right.

15:32.975 --> 15:34.477
Who owes what-what to who?

15:34.519 --> 15:35.854
LUCILLE: <i>Send me some evidence</i>
<i>of a wall</i>

15:35.896 --> 15:37.397
<i>I can show the Chinese.</i>

15:37.438 --> 15:38.565
And the government.

15:38.606 --> 15:40.901
We need to make
this happen, George.

15:40.942 --> 15:42.944
The Chinese have more
than a sharpened noodle

15:42.985 --> 15:44.612
with my name on it.

15:44.654 --> 15:46.698
NARRATOR: <i>And days later,</i>
<i>that evidence arrived</i>

15:46.740 --> 15:48.115
<i>from George Sr.</i>

15:48.157 --> 15:49.659
We've built this wall.

15:49.701 --> 15:51.411
We have miles and...

15:51.452 --> 15:54.581
and miles of wall, uh...

15:54.622 --> 16:00.879
(audio fast-fowarding)

16:00.921 --> 16:03.381
- There's more wall, uh...
- Dad! Dad...!

16:03.423 --> 16:06.092
- And you know, and it feels good to help,
- It's spinning!

16:06.133 --> 16:07.802
to protecting our-our border.

16:07.844 --> 16:09.679
LUCILLE: My God,
he Steamboat Willied it.

16:09.721 --> 16:11.765
- It's a heart project.
- Dad! Dad!

16:11.806 --> 16:13.182
We love America.

16:13.224 --> 16:15.810
- We love America.
- Daddy!

16:15.852 --> 16:18.855
(sighs)

16:18.897 --> 16:22.483
<i>And that's when Lucille noticed</i>
<i>something worrisome.</i>

16:24.151 --> 16:27.113
<i>It seemed her prison family</i>
<i>was preparing</i>

16:27.154 --> 16:30.784
<i>for her to disappear as well.</i>

16:36.456 --> 16:39.667
<i>So Lucille took matters</i>
<i>into her own hands.</i>

16:41.878 --> 16:43.922
GOB: Well, that was fast,
you hot little...

16:43.964 --> 16:46.424
- It's your mother. - Hi, sorry, I
thought you were somebody else.

16:46.466 --> 16:48.092
I can't tell you who, 'cause
I'm-I'm dating someone famous.

16:48.134 --> 16:49.552
someone... famous.

16:49.594 --> 16:51.554
You better start to build
this wall built pronto.

16:51.596 --> 16:54.015
I tried with your father,
but he can't do it.

16:54.056 --> 16:55.934
Well, I'm kind of busy now--
I'm working with Michael.

16:55.976 --> 16:57.978
What are you working on
with Michael?

16:58.019 --> 16:59.646
Dad made him give me a job.

16:59.687 --> 17:01.063
I see--
so he thought it was

17:01.105 --> 17:03.399
a good idea
to have you two together.

17:03.441 --> 17:04.901
Isn't that nice?

17:04.943 --> 17:07.444
My God, is there anyone there
with half a brain

17:07.487 --> 17:08.695
that can help me with this?

17:08.738 --> 17:09.990
I don't know about
"half a brain,"

17:10.031 --> 17:11.531
but Tobias is living
with me right now

17:11.574 --> 17:13.159
and he's not very bright.

17:13.200 --> 17:16.244
Although he is working in
the rehab where Lucille 2 is.

17:16.287 --> 17:17.664
He is?

17:17.704 --> 17:19.205
<i>And that's when Lucille came up</i>

17:19.248 --> 17:20.875
<i>with a plan</i>
<i>to get transferred away</i>

17:20.916 --> 17:22.335
<i>from the Jade Dragon Triad.</i>

17:22.376 --> 17:23.920
Hire a crew and start the wall.

17:23.962 --> 17:25.421
And not a word to your brother.

17:25.463 --> 17:26.923
I'm getting a transfer.

17:26.964 --> 17:29.676
It's time for Mama to put on
the old drunk act.

17:29.717 --> 17:31.385
GOB:
That was an a...?

17:34.138 --> 17:36.057
<i>After a call</i>
<i>to Lucille 2's rehab center,</i>

17:36.098 --> 17:37.809
- (slurring): Lucille 2, please.
<i>- where her drunk act was</i>

17:37.851 --> 17:40.353
<i>as good as you'd see</i>
<i>at the Method One Clinic...</i>

17:40.394 --> 17:42.022
Fine, Lucille Austero.

17:42.063 --> 17:43.982
<i>...Lucille was admitted</i>
<i>as a patient.</i>

17:44.024 --> 17:45.316
<i>And soon met the therapist</i>

17:45.358 --> 17:46.108
<i>who held the keys to her</i>
<i>freedom.</i>

17:46.150 --> 17:47.276
You look great.

17:47.318 --> 17:48.987
That suit looks
very hetero on you.

17:49.029 --> 17:51.865
Well, thank you--
you look very hetero as well.

17:51.906 --> 17:55.201
Now... how are you?

17:55.242 --> 17:56.828
I'm as normal as blueberry pie.

17:56.870 --> 17:59.080
So write that down on a form,
sign me out,

17:59.121 --> 18:01.415
I won't have
to go back to prison,

18:01.457 --> 18:05.252
and maybe you'll find a new car
parked in your driveway.

18:07.213 --> 18:08.631
Oh...

18:08.673 --> 18:10.842
Yes, well,
it-it doesn't work that way.

18:10.884 --> 18:13.678
We have to have a series
of sessions, and, uh, I have to

18:13.720 --> 18:16.180
swear in the best
of my professional opinion

18:16.222 --> 18:18.558
that you have accepted
and made every effort

18:18.599 --> 18:21.310
at thoughtfully reflecting
upon your weaknesses.

18:21.352 --> 18:23.354
Yes!
Write down that I did that.

18:23.396 --> 18:25.023
Well, no,
I-I don't work that way.

18:25.065 --> 18:26.399
You don't work any way.

18:26.440 --> 18:28.192
This is your first paying job
in ten years.

18:28.234 --> 18:29.569
Oh, no, no, this doesn't pay.

18:29.610 --> 18:31.404
This is part of a
work release program.

18:31.445 --> 18:33.606
The state of California thinks
that I'm a sex offender.

18:33.614 --> 18:36.283
D-D-Don't worry about what
the state of California thinks.

18:36.325 --> 18:37.994
The point is we have a chance

18:38.036 --> 18:39.620
to be honest with ourselves.

18:39.662 --> 18:42.540
Fine-- you don't look
heterosexual in that suit.

18:42.582 --> 18:44.918
You look as swishy
as Ryan Seacrest.

18:44.959 --> 18:46.753
Ryan Seacrest is straight.

18:46.794 --> 18:48.880
And I'm 40!
Sign the form.

18:48.922 --> 18:51.049
Well, at least we have
a dialogue going.

18:51.091 --> 18:52.550
Dialogue?

18:52.592 --> 18:54.594
If you don't release me
you've heard the last

18:54.635 --> 18:56.554
I'm going to say to you
in these sessions.

18:56.596 --> 18:58.472
Fine, but you will have
to sit with me

18:58.514 --> 19:00.141
for the full session.

19:00.182 --> 19:02.685
Every single session.

19:02.727 --> 19:07.023
Now, Lucille, I can't
make you talk.

19:07.065 --> 19:09.525
But you know what I can do?

19:15.322 --> 19:17.075
Hmm?

19:19.077 --> 19:22.329
Okay, I can't trick you
into talking, either.

19:22.371 --> 19:24.665
<i>This went on</i>
<i>for several sessions.</i>

19:32.048 --> 19:34.550
Perhaps that's
why they call this place

19:34.592 --> 19:37.720
Au-stare-ity.

19:40.098 --> 19:41.182
No?

19:43.225 --> 19:45.895
Au-stare-i...

19:45.937 --> 19:47.021
Fine.

19:47.063 --> 19:48.064
Well, if you're
not going to talk,

19:48.106 --> 19:49.315
I'm just going to...

19:49.356 --> 19:51.233
- write this up.
<i>- Earlier that day,</i>

19:51.275 --> 19:53.277
<i>Tobias had encountered</i>
<i>a plot problem</i>

19:53.319 --> 19:55.155
<i>with the</i>
<i>"Fantastic Four" musical.</i>

19:55.196 --> 19:56.363
A villain.

19:56.405 --> 19:57.991
I was thinking the same thing.

19:58.032 --> 20:00.743
I mean, why aren't the
Fantastic Four fighting anyone.

20:00.785 --> 20:02.453
Instead of just
dancing around, you mean.

20:02.495 --> 20:04.622
Right, it's like all Sharks
and no Jets.

20:04.664 --> 20:06.666
Then we would have a second act.

20:06.707 --> 20:08.334
Lucia, right?

20:08.375 --> 20:09.836
I mean, that's their foe.

20:09.877 --> 20:11.212
Lucia Von Bardass?

20:12.839 --> 20:15.424
Have you guys ever
even read one of these things?

20:15.466 --> 20:17.844
<i>So Tobias was glad for the</i>
<i>break in Lucille's sessions.</i>

20:17.885 --> 20:18.886
- ...to do this right?
<i>- So that he could work on it.</i>

20:18.928 --> 20:20.387
I mean, really right.

20:20.429 --> 20:22.807
This woman is a villain.

20:22.849 --> 20:24.184
You think I'm a villain, too?

20:24.225 --> 20:25.476
- No...
- My children

20:25.518 --> 20:27.020
are all waiting for me to die

20:27.061 --> 20:28.521
so they can divvy up my stuff,

20:28.562 --> 20:30.481
my Chinese gang mates were
getting ready

20:30.523 --> 20:33.151
to noodle stab me,
and even one of the guards

20:33.193 --> 20:35.195
called me "Gangie,"
and he was talking

20:35.236 --> 20:36.570
about the monster movie.

20:36.612 --> 20:39.032
He thinks that horrible
monster looks like me!

20:39.073 --> 20:41.534
So fine, you want to call me
a villain, I accept it!

20:41.575 --> 20:42.827
I'm your villain!

20:42.869 --> 20:45.038
Uh, actually I was writing down

20:45.079 --> 20:46.080
a casting breakdown

20:46.122 --> 20:47.874
for the role of Lucia

20:47.915 --> 20:49.667
for my "Fantastic Four" musical.

20:49.709 --> 20:52.628
This was all
about your stupid play?

20:52.670 --> 20:54.255
I was about to cry

20:54.296 --> 20:56.423
for the first time in 60 years.

20:56.465 --> 20:58.968
I remember when
the last time was, too.

20:59.010 --> 21:01.929
I hid under Mama's porch
during a thunderstorm...

21:01.971 --> 21:04.140
(voice breaks): and I found
the remains of my ostri...

21:04.182 --> 21:06.642
It's not a stupid play.

21:06.684 --> 21:08.186
It's a musical.

21:08.228 --> 21:09.520
And I have to debut it

21:09.562 --> 21:11.105
on a boat at Cinco.

21:12.314 --> 21:13.649
It's on a boat?

21:13.691 --> 21:15.193
Take to the sea!

21:15.235 --> 21:17.653
Yes, I'll sign everyone out
for the night,

21:17.695 --> 21:20.990
but I guess I'll have to play
the old sea bitch myself.

21:21.032 --> 21:22.616
I'm in.

21:22.658 --> 21:24.326
Really?

21:24.368 --> 21:25.912
Well, that's wonderful.

21:25.953 --> 21:27.914
Well, I think we have made
a breakthrough today.

21:27.955 --> 21:30.041
In the musical, not you.

21:30.083 --> 21:32.793
Oh, God, no, there's miles
of work to do with you. (laughs)

21:32.835 --> 21:35.379
<i>But, of course,</i>
<i>he would make her audition.</i>

21:35.421 --> 21:37.464
<i>So Lucille wrote a song</i>
<i>from the heart.</i>

21:37.506 --> 21:39.133
LUCILLE:
♪ My children despise me ♪

21:39.175 --> 21:40.760
♪ My husband defies me ♪

21:40.801 --> 21:42.344
♪ It doesn't surprise me ♪

21:42.386 --> 21:43.679
♪ The hell with them all ♪

21:43.721 --> 21:45.472
♪ I'll put up a wall ♪

21:45.514 --> 21:47.474
♪ You think I'm a villain ♪

21:47.516 --> 21:48.893
♪ A villain I'll be ♪

21:48.935 --> 21:50.561
♪ My heart is in pain ♪

21:50.603 --> 21:52.563
♪ I just want to flee ♪

21:52.605 --> 21:54.899
♪ From me. ♪

21:56.567 --> 21:57.902
Wonderful.

21:57.944 --> 21:59.279
Terrifying.

21:59.320 --> 22:00.321
Isn't she?

22:00.362 --> 22:01.572
Betty, you can leave.

22:01.614 --> 22:03.407
Lucille, would you please stay?

22:03.449 --> 22:06.286
<i>But staying was the last thing</i>
<i>Lucille had in mind.</i>

22:06.327 --> 22:07.745
- (phone rings)
- LUCILLE: Hello?

22:07.787 --> 22:09.747
MAN: I want to be with you;
I... I have needs.

22:09.789 --> 22:10.706
George, is that you?

22:10.748 --> 22:12.250
<i>It wasn't.</i>

22:12.292 --> 22:14.835
<i>It was Oscar who,</i>
<i>living as George,</i>

22:14.877 --> 22:16.963
<i>- and feeling more amorous...</i>
- (Oscar whistles)

22:17.004 --> 22:20.341
<i>...went to visit Lucille 2</i>
<i>for an afternoon delight.</i>

22:20.382 --> 22:22.593
