26:41.477 --> 26:43.896
<i>And Michael remembered</i>
<i>hearing about that, as well.</i>

26:43.937 --> 26:45.856
Me doth think he hath a lady.

26:45.898 --> 26:49.318
- Oh.
- And they're both a bit of celebrities.

26:49.360 --> 26:51.987
Well, that is odd, because I,
I'm also dating a celebrity.

26:52.029 --> 26:53.239
If I were you,
I'd put a tail on him.

26:53.280 --> 26:55.074
Get a P.I.

26:55.115 --> 26:57.451
Where the hell
am I gonna find a P.I.?

26:57.493 --> 26:58.869
Gene Parmesan...

26:58.911 --> 27:00.538
at your service.

27:00.580 --> 27:01.539
(screaming)

27:01.581 --> 27:02.540
Gene!

27:02.582 --> 27:04.666
He does this to me every time!

27:04.708 --> 27:06.869
- What's he doing here, Mom?
- Oh, he's working for me.

27:06.877 --> 27:07.836
Why'd you scream, then?

27:07.878 --> 27:11.298
I thought he was that guy.

27:13.634 --> 27:15.677
Mm.

27:17.054 --> 27:18.847
NARRATOR:
<i>At Lucille's behest,</i>

27:18.889 --> 27:21.975
<i>Michael borrowed the family</i>
<i>P.I. to follow his brother.</i>

27:22.017 --> 27:24.061
GENE:
He just drove by. Pick me up.

27:24.103 --> 27:26.647
MICHAEL:
This is the great disguise, huh?

27:26.688 --> 27:28.023
Fry cook!

27:28.065 --> 27:29.942
Oh, no, no,
this is my horrible night job.

27:29.983 --> 27:32.069
In fact, I was hoping
you could drop me off

27:32.111 --> 27:33.737
at Chicken Dan's
when we're all done.

27:33.779 --> 27:34.780
Chicken Dan's, huh?

27:34.821 --> 27:36.365
That is embarrassing.

27:36.407 --> 27:38.534
This from a man who's driving
around a mapping car?

27:38.576 --> 27:40.453
You know, I don't even think
these things work.

27:40.494 --> 27:42.413
That's why I rely
on these babies right here--

27:42.455 --> 27:43.747
the old binocs.

27:43.789 --> 27:45.874
Let's see if we can't find
this target.

27:45.916 --> 27:47.918
You know, the great thing
about these is,

27:47.960 --> 27:50.630
there's no software to update...

27:50.671 --> 27:52.381
- Oh, God, what are you doing?
- Sorry.

27:52.423 --> 27:54.049
Oh, these binoculars
make me nauseous.

27:54.091 --> 27:55.217
MICHAEL:
Well, of course they do.

27:55.259 --> 27:56.718
Why don't you just use the maps?

27:56.760 --> 27:59.346
- No.
- We're in a satellite-linked mapping car.

27:59.388 --> 28:02.182
No, no. Sometimes
the old ways are the...

28:02.224 --> 28:03.434
- Hey.
- You-you better pull over.

28:03.476 --> 28:04.644
- All right, hang on.
- Pull over!

28:04.685 --> 28:06.061
One, two.

28:06.103 --> 28:07.104
<i>And while Michael was</i>
<i>waylaid...</i>

28:07.146 --> 28:08.397
One, two...

28:08.439 --> 28:09.315
<i>...Lucille was working</i>
<i>on her tap dancing.</i>

28:09.356 --> 28:10.399
One, two.

28:10.441 --> 28:12.901
♪ You look down on Thing ♪

28:12.943 --> 28:15.112
- One, two...
