28:27.874 --> 28:29.627
<i>- ...on people's feelings.</i>
- Oh, uh,

28:29.669 --> 28:31.545
DeBrie, you might have missed
a step, so...

28:31.587 --> 28:33.880
- Sorry. I think I might...I hurt my leg.
- Oh.

28:33.922 --> 28:36.634
And so, I need some, mm,
Tylenol with c-codeine?

28:36.676 --> 28:38.636
Or maybe
a little morphie morph?

28:38.678 --> 28:40.179
No. DeBrie, come on. (laughs)

28:40.220 --> 28:42.014
Don't you want to get back
on that horse?

28:42.055 --> 28:43.599
Even better!

28:43.641 --> 28:45.476
<i>She was the best</i>
<i>villain casting</i>

28:45.518 --> 28:48.354
<i>since Shirley MacClain</i>
<i>in "Gangie Four."</i>

28:48.395 --> 28:50.189
<i>And on the night of Cinco,</i>

28:50.230 --> 28:51.565
<i>Lucille's escape plans</i>

28:51.607 --> 28:53.775
<i>got a step closer</i>
<i>to completion.</i>

28:53.817 --> 28:57.070
<i>Oscar did indeed borrow a boat</i>
<i>and left it idling,</i>

28:57.112 --> 29:00.949
<i>which unfortunately, was what</i>
<i>this man was looking for.</i>

29:00.991 --> 29:03.494
<i>And Lucille slipped away</i>
<i>from the cast,</i>

29:03.536 --> 29:05.829
<i>looking for her husband.</i>

29:05.871 --> 29:08.457
There you are!

29:08.499 --> 29:10.626
What are you doing here?

29:10.668 --> 29:12.545
What do you mean,
what am I doing here?

29:12.586 --> 29:14.338
We made plans...
to escape on the boat!

29:14.380 --> 29:16.507
I never made plans with you.

29:16.549 --> 29:20.135
But we talked
about it on the phone,

29:20.177 --> 29:21.887
when you were trying
to talk dirty to me.

29:21.928 --> 29:23.347
- Oh.
- What is wrong with you?

29:23.389 --> 29:25.224
This is... this is embarrassing.
Full disclosure.

29:25.265 --> 29:26.726
Uh, that was Oscar,

29:26.767 --> 29:28.769
who may have been the one
you were talking with.

29:28.852 --> 29:31.980
He's been filling in...
for me occasionally.

29:32.022 --> 29:35.651
Filling in?
As in, visiting me?

29:35.693 --> 29:38.487
You sent your brother
to have sex with me?

29:38.529 --> 29:40.197
No, I sent him to listen to you

29:40.239 --> 29:42.241
one time, and then,
he found out about the wall,

29:42.282 --> 29:43.909
and tried to get you
talking about it,

29:43.950 --> 29:46.746
and this was his way
of shutting you up.

29:46.787 --> 29:48.955
- He told you this?
- No, you told me

29:48.997 --> 29:50.332
when I visited.

29:50.374 --> 29:53.210
I got in there
a couple of times... too.

29:53.252 --> 29:54.712
Oh, but not for sex.

29:54.754 --> 29:56.630
I don't have the tiger
in my tank anymore.

29:56.672 --> 29:58.424
Maybe I do need a vacay.

29:58.465 --> 29:59.800
So, tell me about this trip.

29:59.841 --> 30:01.552
That's interesting.
Where we going?

30:01.594 --> 30:03.178
I'll tell you where we're going.

30:03.220 --> 30:04.722
We're going to court.

30:04.764 --> 30:06.848
We're getting a real divorce.

30:06.890 --> 30:09.309
You're out of the marriage.

30:09.351 --> 30:11.186
Lucille...?

30:11.228 --> 30:14.440
<i>And that's when she came</i>
<i>face to face with the man...</i>

30:14.481 --> 30:16.108
<i>...whose face</i>
<i>she'd just faced...</i>

30:16.149 --> 30:17.777
- Are you ready?
- <i>...but it was a different...</i>

30:17.818 --> 30:19.403
<i>- It-it was Oscar.</i>
- Hello, Oscar.

30:19.445 --> 30:21.488
You should get an Oscar
for your portrayal of George

30:21.530 --> 30:23.532
in "Screw the Oblivious
Sister-in-law."

30:23.574 --> 30:26.577
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

30:26.619 --> 30:27.661
You-you got me.

30:27.703 --> 30:29.538
I was gon...
I was gonna tell you.

30:29.580 --> 30:31.832
I was acting
when I pretended to be George,

30:31.873 --> 30:34.000
but I am dead serious when I say

30:34.042 --> 30:37.630
you are the hottest woman
I know.

30:37.671 --> 30:42.468
I'm here tonight because
I want to run away with you.

30:42.509 --> 30:44.010
Oscar. Really?

30:44.052 --> 30:45.763
Of course. What?

30:45.805 --> 30:48.515
Do you think I'm here for the
donkey punch? Which I do love,

30:48.557 --> 30:50.517
and it's the only night
you can get it.

30:50.559 --> 30:53.604
But you are the only woman
for me, Lucille!

30:53.646 --> 30:57.065
Bring me those thin,
pot-stained lips.

30:57.107 --> 30:58.818
Oh, honey.

30:58.859 --> 31:00.653
(both moaning)

31:00.694 --> 31:02.404
- What's this?
- I have no idea.

31:02.446 --> 31:03.947
<i>And that's when she found out</i>
<i>the latest thing</i>

31:03.989 --> 31:06.032
<i>that was hers</i>
<i>that had been claimed.</i>

31:06.074 --> 31:08.577
<i>He'd actually acquired it</i>
<i>earlier that night</i>

31:08.619 --> 31:10.704
<i>when he was... polling</i>
<i>for Lucille 2.</i>

31:10.746 --> 31:13.206
- That, um...
- She's claimed you!

31:13.248 --> 31:15.459
Everyone I know wants
to take everything away from me!

31:15.501 --> 31:16.710
No! That's not true.

31:16.752 --> 31:18.044
I love you.

31:18.086 --> 31:19.963
I don't know if it's the maca.

31:20.005 --> 31:21.715
I've just been so randy lately.

31:21.757 --> 31:24.050
But you're...

31:24.092 --> 31:25.344
you...

31:25.385 --> 31:27.095
you're my kind of Lucille!

31:27.137 --> 31:28.347
Get away from me, you liar.

31:28.388 --> 31:30.474
I can't believe
you were with her.

31:30.516 --> 31:32.142
She's finished.

31:32.184 --> 31:34.645
And the Oscar goes, too!

31:34.687 --> 31:36.021
To...?

31:36.062 --> 31:37.481
Get out of my sight!

31:37.523 --> 31:38.816
<i>She was in an emotional storm</i>

31:38.858 --> 31:40.860
<i>and could have used</i>
<i>a therapist.</i>

31:40.901 --> 31:42.820
- Oh, my God...
- TOBIAS: Lucille!

31:42.862 --> 31:44.822
<i>- When she ran into a therapist</i>
- Where are you going?

31:44.864 --> 31:46.448
<i>who could've used a storm.</i>

31:46.490 --> 31:47.949
To disappear.

31:47.991 --> 31:49.869
That's what everyone
wants me to do.

31:49.910 --> 31:52.830
Lucille!

31:52.872 --> 31:55.040
You are not the villain.

31:55.081 --> 31:57.000
(sighs)

31:57.042 --> 31:58.919
I'm so tired
of being the villain.

31:58.960 --> 32:00.420
Well, those days are over.

32:00.462 --> 32:03.590
What you are
is the Invisible Girl.

32:03.632 --> 32:05.258
You make it impossible
for people

32:05.300 --> 32:07.093
to see you in order
to protect yourself.

32:07.135 --> 32:08.637
<i>And somehow, in that moment,</i>

32:08.679 --> 32:10.055
<i>something changed for her.</i>

32:10.096 --> 32:11.473
I do do that.

32:11.515 --> 32:13.392
And in this way, you launch

32:13.433 --> 32:15.143
sneak attacks,
and you create a force field

32:15.185 --> 32:16.562
to keep people away.

32:16.603 --> 32:18.605
Right! I'm not a villain.

32:18.647 --> 32:20.357
I'm the Invisible Girl!

32:20.399 --> 32:21.901
Yes, that's what I'm saying!

32:21.942 --> 32:25.153
Oh, you know, it's funny...
I never would have

32:25.195 --> 32:28.407
come to this if it hadn't been
for Lucille 2's rehab.

32:28.448 --> 32:31.952
I need to pay her back
for everything she's done to me.

32:31.993 --> 32:34.914
I'm going back to rehab.

32:34.955 --> 32:38.876
I just have
to make one quick stop first.

32:38.918 --> 32:40.586
I don't think we have time.

32:40.627 --> 32:42.228
<i>And that's the night</i>
<i>that Lucille decided</i>

32:42.254 --> 32:43.714
<i>she didn't want</i>
<i>to be invisible anymore.</i>

32:43.756 --> 32:45.465
I've got to do this...

32:45.507 --> 32:47.927
<i>And perhaps, ironically,</i>
<i>it was also</i>

32:47.968 --> 32:52.389
<i>the night that Lucille 2</i>
<i>became the Invisible Girl.</i>

32:52.431 --> 32:54.057
